Vice President Biden expressed his admiration and gratitude to Spanish troops for their service in Afghanistan. He also acknowledged the sacrifices made by their families and expressed condolences for the loss of Spanish servicemen in Haiti. Biden emphasized the importance of working together to combat terrorism and stabilize Afghanistan, and praised Spain's leadership in various international peacekeeping missions. He assured the troops that the United States is committed to caring for those who serve and protecting its citizens from violent extremists. Biden concluded by expressing his pride in the partnership between the United States and Spain and his hope to visit again in the future.